-- Ex-divs to take up to 1.27 points off FTSE 100 on July 2
-- By Tricia Wright
-- Mon Jun 30, 2014 06:24AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, June 30 (Reuters) - The following FTSE 100 <.FTSE> companies will go ex-dividend on Wednesday, after which investors will no longer qualify for the latest dividend payout.

According to Reuters calculations at current market prices, the effect of the resulting adjustment to prices by market-makers would take up to 1.27 points off the index. COMPANY (RIC) DIVIDEND  ESTIMATED(pence)   IMPACTBabcock International   <BAB.L> 16.4 0.3227  British Land<BLND.L> 5.4 0.2162   Burberry<BRBY.L>23.2 0.4068   Royal Mail  <RMG.L> 13.3 0.3263  Among FTSE 250 <.FTMC> companies going ex-dividend are:COMPANY (RIC)  DIVIDEND